t: History of Bridge Logos | Publishing | Bridge Logos
s: Bridge Logos, Inc. was established in 1967 as Logos International Fellowship. Based in Plainfield, New Jersey, its founder, a jeweller by the name of Dan Malachuk, launched the business by publishing The Challenging Counterfeit by Raphael Gasson. A year later he published Run Baby Run by Nicky Cruz.
